items.text: Good coffee here!
Great service and coffee!
Nice place to chill. Love their tiramisu and flat white.
One of the best coffee. The barista seems to be a celebrity, and rightly so.. Great coffee and very helpful staff. Keep it up!!
Iced white
Latte was good but cold brew slightly diluted, taste not strong enough.
What a gem. Smack bang in the middle of Arab town, this art gallery/cafe is urban cool. We has the waffles, pb&j French toast, and pancakes. All delish. Added bonus-real coffee, not americano.
BRB pancakes are awesome.
Good ambience, delicious coffee, chill music, art on the walls. Food is good too! Excited to hear they are expanding their kitchen next year.
Love the space, coffee & desserts. Not forgetting the friendly baristas :)
Cheese cake with caramel and cashew nuts.
Sorry, no more of their specialty available. Too many people. Hard to chat. Too loud and cramped up space.
A nice place to chill out. Great design, delicious coffee & cool atmosphere.
Their coffees never fail!
They were having a photoshoot when we arrived. But the service was great, and they attended to us and made sure we were comfortable. The flat whites and sea salt caramel tart were fantastic too.
Coffee is great here! French toast not bad but peanut butter a bit too sweet for me. I'll visit again for trying their big breakfast!
Perhaps this is my favorite cafe.It's dog friendly!There is WiFi.Here,is the most delicious Portobello Burger$15 of those places where I've already eaten to Singapore.There is the best space for pic!
Crazy GOOD Crab Burger
The pb&j French toast is something special!
I found a fly in my breakfast😷😝 disgusting i will never eat there again...
Nice latte. Long table seating inside. The pork sausages were good, but the big breakfast wasn't so big.
Absolutely love the combination of coconut and french toast. Duck confit was pretty good and rather filling. Affogato was bomb.
Ordered a double espresso, got something resembling a single. Coffee itself wasn't bad but not amazing either. Place feels style over substance.
The Nasi Lemak Burger is like a fried chicken burger topped with nasi lemak condiments and sambal on the side. Nothing special. The latte is not bad. And they only seat complete parties.
Good for an afternoon tea or coffee break.
Ricos desayunos si están cansados de la comida Indonesia-Malasia-China pidan huevos con salsa holandesa!
never leave this place until you've tried Peanut Butter & Jelly French Toast
Interesting space with great coffee, sandwiches and cakes! Friendly and helpful crew as well! The barista is awesome and makes great latte art!
The big breakfast or get the scrambled eggs with toast. You will be happy.
Make sure you are not too hungry. 30-45 mins wait for food. Nice place tho.
Great place to chillout for coffee and/or lunch. They only accept cash or credit card.
Yummy coffee and cakes!
The Cherry Peach Cheese Cake is a must Try . Not so sweet n It's a good Combination with a pot tea!! 
We liked the coffee.
Very good soy flat white. The cherry/apricot cheesecake was okay, prettier than it tasted!
Cappuccino and scrambled eggs were very good! Must try ❤️
This place was the only drink place on Victoria street opened late on Saturday night!
Nice atmosphere n good service.
Get here before 1 on weekends to avoid the queue and waiting for seats :-)
Great coffee and delicious Acai bowl. Very cosy for nice weekend breakfast
I love the live music!
Good coffee but the sandwiches could be better.
Espresso.  nice environment
A nice place to chill out. Must try their Tiramisu
Good coffee..great atmosphere. Flat white is very creamy. Cakes have good flavor but might be a bit dry. Recommend ginger and lemongrass cold tea.
Great coffee, priced lower than Symmetry.
The coffee is really good. Both the cappuccino and the flat white were well made.  It's cute and the staff is very nice.
Probably the best cheesecake I've ever had 😍
Delicious cheesecake! The test of coffee is excellent. Coffee latte can be prepared from soy milk. The average bill for coffee and desserts for two-25$
Overpriced
A great chili crab burger, decent espresso drinks, and wifi (that mostly worked).
A super cool and hip cafe with quality coffee and good Western food--come here if you're hankering for kale, whole grain toast, etc!
Best coffee I have had outside Australia!!!! Amazing brekky and cool decor. A must if you are in singa!
Check their Facebook page for schedule of live band  performances, usually in the evening 8pm till late. Source: Straits Times
Lemon poppy cake + zucchini cake !!! Miam miam :P
Service can be a bit slow, but the flat whites are worth the wait.
Loved this place. Gotta have their Chili Crab burger. Try their signature drinks too
Love the lemon poppy seed cake
Generally a much better red velvet cake than Maison. Plus their coffee was not a bad accompaniment at all.
Wifi Password is now Artistry with capital 'A'
Chat coffee at downtime with friendly barista Tim, to get more than coffee often life-imitating-art tips. And oh, the double-ristretto Gibraltar is not bad.
Nice interior with friendly staff. Super like this place
Great space, great food, great service!
All-day bfast menu avail Tue-Fri 9am-9pm, Sat, Sun & PH 9:30am-3pm
Wonderful café, delicious coffee!
Simple and relaxing ambiance. Cool place to hang out with friends and enjoy the good food.
When you're in the washroom… look up!
PB&J French toast...
Very small cafe with decent food (depends what you choose) for one I love the smoked duck croissant.
chili crab burger is a must

Nice place with a nice atmosphere.Unfortunately kitchen is only available until 2:30,I unfortunately have not tasted  it yet.Anyway, there are nice coffee and tasty deserts.average bill for coffee 22$
The WiFi password is artistry.
salted caramel & bacon waffles is a must
My friend literally had orgasm after putting the French toast into his mouth...
PB and J French toast - come early before they get snapped up!
As a photographer myself. There isn't anything I don't like here. You get the gallery, handmade saucers, beer, good coffee and good music. Even though the eggs beans sausage was average.
Red velvet cake, sea salt choc cake & tiramisu are must tries :)
Egg benedict is disappointing.
Food and coffee are good, unfortunately some of the staff aren't overly friendly.
Famous for "Chili Crab Burger"! Never seen this in town before. Try French toast for dessert. Both choices will complete your day.
Consistently good food but limited quantities of each dish - show up in good time for the respective meal. Not a place for a late weekend brunch. Also they need to look up the meaning of "all day".
I like this cappuccino here, this is one of the cafe I willing to return. The shop is good to casual talk and the coffee taste is the one I like as the "Forty Hands".
Welcoming baristas and live acappella jam on Sunday. Nice!
The food, coffee and atmosphere are great but they have the slowest internet in Singapore so it's useless for working in. Maybe by design.
Отличный кофе и паста с лобстером
Weird menu: typical weekend brunch items are not served on weekend, breakfast options are boring. Crab burger is good, although fries are a bit on a dry side. Coffee is great!
Bitcoin accepted! The mocha, the breakfasts, the desserts, the drinks... Order anything and you'll be happy. Oh, and stick around after hours. The events are cool as hell.
Had a very tasty flat white and the food looked delicious
Great carrot cake
Red velvet
Flat whites are super good :) A must have!
French toast. Nuff said.
It is not on the menu but the roast beef sandwich is awesome! Red velvet cake is worth a try too.
It's a good place for catching up with people as the coffee is good and it's fairly quiet.
very good environment and a must try for they French toast, could do some improvement on coffee, but still loving this place
Ask for secret stuff like cold brew and filter coffee! Also, look up when in the toilet.
The Crab Burger and the Duck Confit Pasta are really good. Affogato is excellent. The Coffee in the Iced Cafe Latte is a bit too bitter for my taste overall it was an AWESOME Saturday Lunch.
serves good coffee
Coffee is good. Food is average. Price is average.
The cappuccino and flat white are exceptional here. Definitely worth the trip.
When coffee meets art gallery.
Love the bleach wood rusticity of the gallery, with events & occasional gigs. Indoor or outdoor areas are super. Liberty coffee supply creative thought, & don't even get me started with the convos.
Their baked eggs are my favourite thing to eat at the moment. Very good coffee. Transitions into a bar as the sun sets. Well executed concept.
Quirky well-lit space with some art pieces for sale. Waffles are abit pricey for the portion served with maple syrup.
Great coffee and pastries. The ever changing artwork within the cafe is a bonus too.
Awesome cafe, great food and even better coffee. Must try the Artistry Chilli Crab Burger and the PB&J French Toast- delicious!
Cyprus Salad is great!
Affogato is the BEST in town! A MUST HAVE!
Friendly cafe with free wifi!
Possibly the best coffee in Singapore during the day, great beer and wine in the evenings, occasional live music events and exhibitions, outdoor seating, great service and free wi-fi. 'Nuff said.
Their house burger, Artistry Crab Burger must try! Very nice latte!
Go early! I went there twice around 1pm and they were out of a lot of things. The Truffle fries were delish! Definitely one of the best cafes in town.
Good coffee and location.
Breakfast salads and coffee are awesome. Outdoor seating is lovely as well.
The flat white is pretty good and there is free wifi.
Overrated and incompetent staff Ex: Cappuccino was a Latte  that might not matter much coffee/milk wise but there is a clear distinction between both, they seem to not know it here...
The big breakfast is nice. Coffee is a must
Horrible and sluggish service, took them an hour+ to deliver all items. Worst of all, forgetting orders citing it as 'miscommunication', no apology from the staff. Never coming here again.
Perfect for a nice casual brunch! Love the art pieces and deco inside. Next time i'm definitely trying the yogurt ice cream and granola!
The coffee here is fantastic - they use Liberty coffee beans, which I love. The creamy chicken pasta is great too
Une belle halte entre little India et Arab street - les serveurs sont adorables
These guys have got their shit together. They can even get the food out when there's queue's out the door. They've fixed their WiFi!
Please arrive early if you prefer indoor settings to avoid the outdoor sun. No service charge or GST so do drop a tip or two if you enjoyed their service or food! Love the PBJ French toast!
Foodbis nice
Like it..;)
For those who love coffee, this is a place you can't miss! :)
Prices for the drinks are pretty steep!
Coffee, potato hash
Lovely service and nice interior. The eggplant sandwich was really good. Free wifi and great Austrian beer. Some hipster audience though. ;-)
Chilli crab burger. Think it's quite brilliant combination, to use buns to sop up the chilli crab sauce, and dip it with what I can only describe as pulled crab patty. Awesome fries too!
Sterile interior. Outside seating is good. Chili crab burger was a bit too sweet.
Love the earthenware used to serve the food. Nice presentation, kinda Zen. At least 90% crab meat in crab burger patty. Mushrooms, scrambled eggs & sauté garlic spinach in big breakfast were good
Both the big breakfast and ice latte were absolutely scrumptious. Sitting outside at 12pm and it's not even warm.
Awesome cheese cake!
Their cakes are lovely and change every day. Good service, great ambience.
The Chilli Crab Burger is awesome!
Best Red Velvet Cake in SINGAPORE!
great cakes!
The lemon poppy seed cake and peach/cherry cake are divine. Great coffee.
Very nice concept of a coffee spot. You can enjoy great coffee with art on the walls all around! Super!
